These apps change the way we
work and do things that were

00:01:06.470 --> 00:01:09.100
not even possible before.

00:01:11.190 --> 00:01:15.730
There are several great ways that
we provide for you to get your apps

00:01:15.810 --> 00:01:20.700
into the hands of the end users and
the businesses that you are serving.

00:01:20.870 --> 00:01:24.210
We've got the App Store.

00:01:24.390 --> 00:01:29.000
It's the largest collection
of curated apps anywhere,

00:01:29.000 --> 00:01:31.840
and it's super simple to use.

00:01:31.910 --> 00:01:35.050
Everyone has it on their iOS device.

00:01:35.880 --> 00:01:41.080
Now the apps in the App Store are great,
but they tend to appeal

00:01:41.080 --> 00:01:43.540
to a broad audience,
right?

00:01:44.700 --> 00:01:48.660
Some businesses require apps
that are a little bit more

00:01:49.090 --> 00:01:51.680
specific to their industry.

00:01:51.680 --> 00:01:55.670
And for them,
we have an enterprise in-house program.

00:01:56.140 --> 00:01:57.900
Some of you may have heard of this.

00:01:57.900 --> 00:02:03.160
It's a program where an enterprise
can develop their own apps.

00:02:03.800 --> 00:02:07.900
and distributed within their
organization without review from Apple.

00:02:08.030 --> 00:02:13.420
So these are two great ways to
deliver business apps to your clients.

